parameters.description:
JSON array of filter conditions. Each filter includes: - `key`: Field to filter (e.g., `role`, `country`, `city`, `supplier_id`, `department`, `preferred_contact_method`, `missing_fields`) - `operation`: Filter operation (`eq`, `in`, `gt`, etc.) - `value`: Filter value (can be a string, number, or array) - `group`: Optional. Grouping logic for the filter (`and` or `or`, defaults to `and`). Example: ```json [
    {"key":"role","operation":"eq","value":"manager","group":"and"},
    {"key":"missing_fields","operation":"in","value":["department","description"],"group":"or"}
] ```

JSON array of filter conditions. Filter keys: date, sales_channel_id, location_id, net_items_sold, net_items_sold_by_channel, gross_sales, net_sales, total_sales, returned_units, return_rate, sell_through_rate, lost_sales_units, missed_revenue, category, shopify_tags. Numeric keys support gte/lte. Example - filter variants with missed revenue >= $100: ```json [
    {"key": "date", "operation": "gte", "value": "2024-12-01"},
    {"key": "date", "operation": "lte", "value": "2024-12-31"},
    {"key": "missed_revenue", "operation": "gte", "value": 100}
] ```

JSON array of filter conditions. Each filter includes: - `key`: Field to filter (e.g., `name`, `status`, `adjustment_type`, `start_date`, `end_date`). - `operation`: Filter operation (`eq`, `gte`, `lte`, `in`, `like`, etc.). - `value`: Filter value (can be a string, number, or array). Example: ```json [
    {"key": "status", "operation": "eq", "value": "active"},
    {"key": "adjustment_type", "operation": "in", "value": ["CHANGE", "VALUE"]}
] ```

JSON array of filter conditions. Each filter includes: - `key`: Field to filter (e.g., `variant_id`, `location_id`) - `operation`: Filter operation (`eq`, `in`, `gt`, etc.) - `value`: Filter value (can be a string, number, or array) Example: ```json [
    {"key":"variant_id","operation":"eq","value":"12345678"},
    {"key":"location_id","operation":"in","value":["1234","5678"]}
] ```
